-name\">conduct a trademark search<\/a> with the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.uspto.gov\/\">U.S. Patent and Trademark Office<\/a> to ensure your name is available for use.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency#how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency-section6-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-search-the-usptos-trademark-database-288x288-20200703.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"3","name":"<p>Perform a name availability search with the state.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Once you've confirmed that your business is available with the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office, you have to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.namesnack.com\/guides\/how-to-check-if-a-business-name-is-available-for-free\">check with your local state department<\/a> to verify if the name has already been registered. If not, you can trademark your business name and register it will the state department.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency#how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency-section6-step3","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-search-the-sosdirect-288x288-20200619_2023-09-27-011644_apxl.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"7","name":"<p>Form your social media marketing company.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Choose a business entity.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>You have the choice of registering your business as a corporation, sole proprietorship, partnership, or Limited Liability Company (LLC). Because your business will likely not require a corporate office or shareholders, we recommend starting out with a sole proprietorship, which may not require official registration.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency#how-to