general business license when you officially start your business, though. Go to the Small Business Administration (SBA) site to check for <a href=\"https:\/\/www.sba.gov\/business-guide\/launch-your-business\/apply-licenses-permits\">state licenses and permits<\/a> you may need.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency#how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency-section7-step4","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-license-and-permits-288x288-20200729_2023-09-27-012008_vnyn.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"8","name":"<p>Get funding.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Ask family and friends.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>One of the more common options is asking family and friends to invest in your business. Prepare a well-informed presentation and include your business plan.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency#how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency-section8-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-ask-friends-and-family-288x288-20200728.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Apply for a loan with the Small Business Administration (SBA).<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Managed by the SBA, these loans help businesses with limited financial alternatives to access funding at low-interest rates through federally-backed lending.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency#how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency-section8-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-an-sba-loan-288x288-20200724_2023-09-27-012220_vepr.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"3","name":"<p>Apply for a small business loan.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Small business lending includes microloans, bank loans, credit cards, venture capital, and SBA-backed loans. Your social media marketing agency can use a small business loan to purchase equipment and more.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency#how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency-section8-step3","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-a-small-business-loan-288x288-20200728_2023-09-27-012325_zvcs.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"4","name":"<p>Get a business credit card.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>If your business is less than two-years-old and you have a good credit record, your chances of qualifying for a business credit card are good. A business credit card is great for small expenses that need to be handled immediately.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency#how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency-section8-step4","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-a-business-credit-card-288x288-20200728.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"9","name":"<p>Search for clients.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Reach out to prospective clients in your niche.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Find out what potential clients are doing in terms of marketing and find out if you can help them with their online marketing. Explain to them how their online presence can grow brand loyalty, which ensures ongoing sales.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency#how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency-section9-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-reach-out-to-potential-clients-288x288-20200728.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Know your prospective client. Research them online, which helps you to prepare your pitch.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Have high-quality and convincing sales-ready messages or call scripts.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Choose your timing carefully when you make contact.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Ask them the right diagnostic questions.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Have a clear picture of the services you are offering.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Have persuasive proposals and presentations.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Ensure your social media marketing agency has an effective and simple sales process.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Offer a free audit.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>A great way to attract clients is by offering them <strong>a free digital audit to show them an overview of their current online efforts<\/strong> and how you can help them improve. Include relevant data and analytics that details their current online presence and their potential brand development if they use your services.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency#how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency-section9-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-offer-a-free-audit-288x288-20200728.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"3","name":"<p>Create a company website.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>List all relevant information customers may be interested in, such as prices, services, and contact information. If possible, include testimonials from previous clients.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency#how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency-section9-step3","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-create-a-company-website-288x288-20200728_2023-09-27-012836_grut.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"10","name":"<p>Hire employees.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Decide if you need to hire employees.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>When starting out, it's not recommended to hire a team of employees. It's best to first establish a solid client base and grow your business. However, as your social media marketing agency grows you may need a personal or virtual assistant, an accountant, and multiple account managers.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency#how-to-start-a-social-media-marketing-agency-section10-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-decide-if-you-need-to-hire-additional-employees-288x288-20200723_2023-09-27-012938_mlmc.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>You can use hiring software to advertise positions for your social media marketing business.<\/p>\n"}]}]}]}</script> <div
class="block block-pros-cons"><h2 id=pros-and-cons>Pros and Cons:</h2><div
class="row pros-cons-wrapper"><div
class="col-md-6"><div
class="pros-cons pros"><div
class="heading">Pros</div><ul
class="list list-unstyled"><li>Inexpensive to start.</li><li>You can have fun while you are working.</li><li>You can work from anywhere.</li><li>You don&#039;t need staff.</li><li>There is a growing need for social media managers.</li></ul></div></div><div
class="col-md-6"><div
class="pros-cons cons"><div
class="heading">Cons</div><ul
class="list list-unstyled"><li>It&#039;s a balancing act — you need to balance multiple clients&#039; social media accounts simultaneously.</li><li>Some businesses don&#039;t understand the importance of social media marketing.</li></ul></div></div></div></div><div
